At the moment statuses are displayed just like any other content. Statuses aren't like other content so they should be displayed differently in search results.

See http://www.openehr.org/wiki/display/spec/openEHR+Templates+and+Specialised+Archetypes
Go aout 1/3 the way down, you can see inside some preformat blocks text like the following, where we have tried to quote syntax like {*} and {0}, but to no avail - inside preformat blocks it apparently does not work  This is preventing us from displaying some of our most basic content on the web.


ELEMENT[at0003] ∈ {
	value ∈ {
		DV_QUANTITY ∈ \{*\}
		DV_INTERVAL ∈ \\{*\\}
                DV_COUNT ∈ \\{*\\}
		DV_INTERVAL ∈ \\{*\\}
	        }
}

 
The intention is to remove the DV_INTERVAL<*> alternatives. This is achieved by redefining the enclosing object to removed the relevant types:

ELEMENT[at0003.1] ∈ {
	value ∈ {
		DV_INTERVAL occurrences ∈ \\{0\\}
                DV_INTERVAL<DV_COUNT> occurrences ∈ \\{0\\}
        }
}

