Right now we append all the text we want to be indexed and searched to a field called "contentBody". Unfortunately this is the same field we use to display the excerpt. So in case the actual text on the wiki page is not very long we end up displaying stuff like the version comment and whatever else we append to the "contentBody".
We should rather split that and only use the actual body content for the excerpt and have a special bucket field where we just put all the text we want to be indexed and searched.

